I was afraid choosing "no problem" would ed the task before it was completed.  Turns out it doesn't, and you can still tell it what to do next.

I think sometimes it would be nicer to just be able to tell it what to do next and not have to try to  come up with a problem first. like once the cup is visible, I didn't know if it would just then pick it up and finish the job or if it wouldn't know what to do since it was in  different location. It would be nice to just tell it to pick it up, and if it doesn't then move to the couch, then worry about there being a problem.  Similarly after that to just tell it to move to the couch if needed.  I guess if it is stopped and you are asking us there is still a problem, but I'd just rather handle it the other way I think.
